# AI engineering stack (profile-page)

Read `docs/AI-WORKFLOW-PLAYBOOK.md` for full handoff patterns.

## Tool split

- **Cursor (you):** Implement code, multi-file edits, tests, Semgrep fixes, OTEL hooks, workflow YAML in this repo, Dependabot branch fixes.
- **Claude:** Architecture plans, CI log analysis, Semgrep rule design, Grafana dashboard design, dependency risk review, multi-repo docs — user brings plans here for execution.

## Stack

- **CI:** Thin wrappers in `.github/workflows/` call `aaron-howard/ci-templates` (`semgrep.yml`, `ci.yml`, `e2e.yml` on `@main`). Workflow logic changes usually go in **ci-templates**, not duplicated here.
- **Semgrep:** Custom rules in `config/semgrep/rules/`. Run locally: `semgrep scan --config p/ci --config p/typescript --config p/nodejs --config config/semgrep/rules`.
- **OTEL:** `config/otel/`, `src/lib/observability/`, spans in `hooks.server.ts` and `$lib/server/db`. Opt-in via `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_*` env vars.
- **Git:** Never commit to `main`. Branch → PR → merge.

## Before finishing

Run `npm run lint` and `npm test` when code changed. Match `CLAUDE.md` conventions. Do not commit unless the user asks.
